# Backend Env Template Index
#
# Backend env owns DB credentials, provider secrets, runtime layout, and
# training/review settings. Do not put these values in frontend env files.
#
# Local backend-only development reference:
#   backend/.env.local.example
#
# Production backend deployment reference:
#   backend/.env.prod.example
#
# Spring Boot does not automatically load `backend/.env`; use platform env,
# root `.env` with the provided scripts, or explicitly source a copied file.
